Ferreting out Deep Throat's identity has long been a favorite topic in Washington and beyond, and the search has engaged former Nixon administration officials who dealt with the consequences of his leaks, intrepid journalism students eager to solve one of a prior generation's abiding enigmas, and many an armchair sleuth. Others have focused on specific individuals, doggedly studying who might have had access to what kind of information, and cross-referencing that detective work with other sources, including the book by Woodward and Bernstein upon which the film was based. Another strain of thought focused on officials in the FBI. 